African Swine Flu Found in Hogs in Nothern Russia, Food Safety Group Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-06T07:06:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/african-swine-flu-found-in-hogs-in-nothern-russia-food-safety-group-says.html
African swine fever was found in
hogs in the northern Russian region of Murmansk, according to
 Rosselkhoznadzor , the food safety watchdog.  The virus was found in several pigs in the Severomorsk
settlement and the entire herd of 21 animals has been
slaughtered, Rosselkhoznadzor said in an e-mailed statement
today. Veterinarians are investigating.  Three cases were found in and around  St. Petersburg  in
January. Most other cases have been found in southern areas.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  